            "end_cfi": "/2/4/102/1:479",
            "format": "EPUB",
            "highlighted_text": "The second interpretation of “experiencing the whole body” is found in the Buddhist commentaries, which say that this phrase refers to the whole “breath body.” This means that we train experiencing the beginning, middle, and end of each breath",
